article.headline: Carey, Texas notch 16th straight victory

article.linkText: Carey makes memorable return to Stanford court
article.story:
MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- Lindsay Whalen scored 17 points and Janel
McCarville added 15 as Minnesota got a 77-57 exhibition win on
Wednesday over Zala Volan, a Hungarian professional club.

Kadidja Andersson added 10 points for Minnesota. She and
McCarville had 11 rebounds each.

The Gophers used several lineups in an effort to get playing
time for freshmen Kelly Roysland, Jamie Broback and Liz Podominick,
who combined for 17 points.

Jana Lichnerova led scoring for Zala Volan, with 14 points.
Anita Heller added 12 and Marie Ruzickova added 10.

Minnesota scored 50 points in the first half, but cooled in the
second as field goal and three-point shooting each dropped to 33.3
percent. Zala Volan scored 36 points in the first half.
